<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
TYPE LOCALITY. Originally “haud procul a Karman in 
<collectingCountry box="[762,830,223,248]" name="Iran" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Persia</collectingCountry>
meridionali” [= near 
<collectingRegion box="[1072,1162,224,247]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Kerman</collectingRegion>
in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1301,1376,223,248]" name="Iran" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Persia</collectingCountry>
]. 
<bibRefCitation author="Das, I. &amp; Dattagupta, B. &amp; Gayen, N. C." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="121 - 172" refId="ref48844" refString="Das, I., Dattagupta, B. &amp; Gayen, N. C. (1998) History and catalogue of reptile types in the collection of the Zoological Survey of India. Journal of South Asian Natural History, 3, 121 - 172." type="journal article" year="1998">
Das 
<emphasis box="[151,209,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
(1998)
</bibRefCitation>
specified the locality to “Saadatabad, S. W. of Karman, 
<collectingCountry box="[940,1011,260,285]" name="Iran" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Persia</collectingCountry>
” perhaps based on the note by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, M. A." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref65609" refString="Smith, M. A. (1935) The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Reptilia and Amphibia. Vol. II. Sauria. Taylor and Francis, Ltd., Red Lion Court, Fleet Street, London, 440 pp. [Reprint Edition 1974, Today and Tomorrow's Printers and Publishers]" type="book" year="1935">Smith (1935)</bibRefCitation>
, p. 348.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[151,560,332,357]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
