<collectingCountry box="[350,397,332,355]" name="Iran" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Iran</collectingCountry>
, SW 
<collectingCountry box="[458,557,332,357]" name="Pakistan" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3342274561" country="Iran" location="Baluchistan Prov." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Khorasan-e Shomali">
DISTRIBUTION IN 
<collectingCountry box="[350,406,368,391]" name="Iran" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">IRAN</collectingCountry>
. 
<figureCitation box="[421,517,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 128–133. 128" captionStartId="93.[151,264,1557,1580]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,213,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-79@93.[151,1436,193,1536]" captionTargetPageId="93" captionText="FIGURES 128–133. 128. Ablepharus pannonicus. 129. Chalcides ocellatus. 130. Eumeces schneiderii. Red symbols represent records of E. s. princeps, blue of E. s. zarudnyi and blue square denotes its type locality, violet question mark indicates dubious data for E. blythianus. 131. Eurylepis taeniolatus. 132. Ophiomorus blanfordii. 133. Ophiomorus brevipes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929775/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 133</figureCitation>
. Most records are from along the Afghan and Pakistani border (
<collectingRegion box="[1234,1343,367,392]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Shomali" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Khorasan</collectingRegion>
Razavi, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,333,404,429]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Jonubi" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">South Khorasan</collectingRegion>
, Sistan and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C387F2FFA1FF94FF5B4FB555D5FDB4:8EB5603FFFA1FF94FE1F4EB654E6FE01" box="[467,670,404,429]" country="Iran" name="Baluchistan Prov." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" stateProvince="Khorasan-e Shomali">Baluchistan Prov.</location>
), other records are from 
<collectingRegion box="[946,1039,404,427]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Kerman</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1050,1185,404,428]" country="Iran" name="Hormozgan" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Hormozgan</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1244,1402,404,429]" country="Iran" name="Semnan" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Semnan Prov.</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[151,943,439,464]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
